explains: v. 处在……之前，先于；在……之前做（或说）；比……更重要，比……（级别）更高

sentences.en: He gestured to Alice to precede them from the room.
sentences.cn: 他示意艾丽斯从房间里出来走在他们前面。

sentences.en: Capitalize all proper nouns but not the articles (a, an) that precede them.
sentences.cn: 把所有的专有名词大写，它们之前的冠词(a, an)则不用。

sentences.en: This factor must precede an ice age and have the effect of slightly lowering Earth's temperature.
sentences.cn: 这一因素一定出现在冰川期之前，并有稍微降低地球温度的效果。
